13.11	Kirov_Ballet	Mariinsky Ballet	The Mariinsky Ballet is a classical ballet company based at the Mariinsky Theatre in Saint Petersburg, Russia. Founded in the 18th century and originally known as the Imperial Russian Ballet, the Mariinsky Ballet is one of the world's leading ballet companies. Internationally, the Mariinsky Ballet is most commonly known by its former Soviet name the Kirov Ballet, a title which is still used by the company when touring. The Mariinsky Ballet is the parent company of the Vaganova Ballet Academy, a leading international ballet school.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/0/05/Mariinsky_Theatre_Logo.png/300px-Mariinsky_Theatre_Logo.png
